data.content:
## What breaks: Sync I/O on EF Core Cosmos DB is **fully removed** in .NET 11

In .NET 10, sync methods like `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, and `SaveChanges()` were unsupported by default on the Cosmos DB provider but could be re-enabled with an opt-in. **In EF Core 11, that opt-in is gone** — calling any sync I/O API **always throws**, no matter what.

### Your code must become async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

### Key mapping

| .NET 10 (sync) | .NET 11 (must use) |
|---|---|
| `ToList()` | `await ToListAsync()` |
| `First()` | `await FirstAsync()` |
| `Count()` | `await CountAsync()` |
| `SaveChanges()` | `await SaveChangesAsync()` |

This will ripple up through your call chain — all callers of these repository methods will also need to become `async`/`await`. Tracking issue: [dotnet/efcore#37059](https://github.com/dotnet/efcore/issues/37059).
